A biker is on a road trip starting at altitude 0. You are given an integer array gain of length n where gain[i] is the net gain in altitude between points i and i + 1. Return the highest altitude reached.

Python:
class Solution:
    def largestAltitude(self,g):
        a=0
        m=0
        for x in g:
            a+=x
            if a>m:
                m=a
        return m

Java:
class Solution {
    public int largestAltitude(int[] g) {
        int a=0,m=0;
        for(int x:g){
            a+=x;
            if(a>m) m=a;
        }
        return m;
    }
}
